                  Derivácia 



(c)&#039; = 0
(x^a)&#039; = ax^{a-1}
(x)&#039; = 1
(\sin x)&#039; = \cos x
(\cos x)&#039; = -\sin x
(\tan x)&#039; = {1 \over \cos^2x}
(\cot x)&#039; = {-1 \over \sin^2x}
(\sin^{-1}x)&#039; = {1 \over \sqrt{1-x^2}}
